Agip, Shell, Total to Sell 45% of Nigeria Licence to Elcrest

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-03-31T22:02:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-31/agip-shell-total-to-sell-45-of-nigeria-licence-to-elcrest.html
Eland Oil & Gas Ltd.  said its joint
venture with  Starcrest Nigeria Energy Ltd.,  Elcrest Exploration
and Production Nigeria Ltd., won the auction to buy a 45 percent
stake in Licence OML 40, located in the  Niger Delta , from Shell
Petroleum Development Company of Nigeria Ltd., Total E&P Nigeria
Ltd. and Nigerian Agip Oil Company Ltd., Eland said in an e-
mailed statement today. The agreement must be approved by the
Nigerian government before being completed, the statement said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 